als provides individualized patient care. Our staff includes experts in surgical specialties who are highly trained through an intense orientation program, in-service training, and continuing education programs. Our compassionate surgical team at ALMH is highly skilled and ready to provide you with the best possible care. Prior to your scheduled surgery, we encourage ALMH surgical patients to download our Surgery Preparation Guide. This guide provides more information about what you can expect before and after surgery. Download Surgery Preparation Guide It is our goal to provide you with excellent service and a great patient experience. ALMH is dedicated to providing you with individual attention before, during and after your surgery to keep you as comfortable as possible. Please remember, if you have any questions, it’s OK to ask any ALMH staff member. Read below for more information about the range of surgical services offered at ALMH: Anesthesia Services Anesthesia is used so that surgery and other medical procedures can be performed without unnecessary pain. The goal of the ALMH Anesthesia Department is to provide safe anesthesia care for inpatients and outpatients of all ages, from newborn to the elderly. Anesthesia care is provided by a team of Certified Registered Nurse Anesthetists and Anesthesiologists. The anesthesia team administers general anesthesia, spinal, epidurals, intravenous sedation, PICC line insertions and regional blocks (ankle and axillary, etc.). Anesthesia services are provided in the surgery, obstetrical, endoscopy, emergency room and other departments throughout the hospital. Ear, Nose, Throat (ENT) A variety of surgeries are performed to assist patients with ear, nose and throat conditions. Procedures can include tonsillectomy, adenoidectomy and myringotomy tube insertion. General Surgery Laparoscopic technology (visualization of internal organs with a telescope inserted through a small abdominal incision) is routinely used for diagnosis and treatment of disease. Laparoscopic techniques may be used to remove the gallbladder, appendix, and for hernia repair. A wide range of procedures for cancer of the colon, liver, breast and other anatomical sites are performed in conjunction with the care provided to patients who come to the hospital. Sentinel node mapping technology can also be used to identify lymph nodes in breast and melanoma cancers. As an aspect of regional organ and tissue banking, various organs and tissues can be harvested at ALMH. Gynecologic/Reproductive A full range of services are available for patients needing gynecologic surgery. Laparoscopic procedures are performed both for diagnostic purposes and operative treatment. CO2 laser therapy is available for treatment if needed. Dilation and curettage, thermal balloon, endometrial ablation, operations for prolapse and incontinence, removal of benign tumors, and vaginal or abdominal hysterectomies are some of the common gynecologic surgeries performed. Malignancies involving the reproductive organs, including cancer of the cervix, uterus, and ovaries can also be treated. Ophthalmology We provide outpatient ophthalmic services for patients of varying ages. Occuloplastic procedures offer plastic reconstruction for patients of all ages. Cataract surgery is frequently performed on patients in the aging population. Visit our Ophthamology Services page to learn more. Orthopedic Surgery Orthopedic surgical services are provided to patients who may have injuries, diseases/disorders, and degenerative conditions affecting the musculoskeletal system. ALMH patients benefit from advanced technologies and our highly skilled surgical team. We perform total joint replacements using a variety of instrumentation and implants based on individual patient need. If pain or arthritis is limiting your everyday activities, orthopedic surgery and our acclaimed JointWorks program can help. Our team delivers an experienced approach to total knee and hip replacements and advanced orthopedic care. We’ll guide you through pre-surgery education and post-surgery rehab so that you can return to your life. Visit Orthopedic Services page for more information. Podiatry Podiatric services treat ailments of the foot and ankle. Podiatrists within the community perform surgical procedures using the most current technology available to the bones of the feet and ankle. Podiatric surgical services help relieve pain associated with foot deformities and improve function of the foot and ankle. Our ALMH team also offers surgical treatment of ulcers and wounds associated with diabetic foot management. Urology ALMH provides a full range of urological services for patients seeking diagnostic, treatment or surgical intervention for conditions of the genitourinary system. Some urological procedures can be performed using various endoscopes to visualize the bladder, ureter and kidneys. Transvaginal taping techniques improve or restore urinary continence. To contact the ALMH Surgery Department, please call 217-605-5306. Showing: Surgery Show All Services Surgery Cardiology Services Clinical Nutrition Services Diabetes Self-Management Education Program Memorial Diabetes Services at ALMH Colonoscopy Diabetes Education Management Clinical Nutrition Services Diabetes Self-Management Education Program Memorial Diabetes Services at ALMH Diagnostic Imaging Schedule an Exam Abdominal Ultrasound Barium Enema CT Scan 3D Digital Mammography Intravenous Pyelgram Magnetic Resonance Imaging (MRI) Obsetrical Ultrasound Pediatric Voiding Cystorethogram (VCUG) Pelvic Ultrasound Upper GI Series Emergency Services Emergency Stroke Care Family Maternity Suite Education and Support Admission to ALMH Before Your Return Home WebNursery Heart & Vascular Services Emergency Heart Care Outpatient Heart Failure Clinic Cardiovascular Tests Our Team Symptoms and Risk Factors Heart Blog Podcasts Contact Us Cardio Pulmonary Rehabilitation Hospice Hospitalist Program Infusion Therapy